{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Step 4: Detect (yes/no)\n",
    "\n",
    "![Step 4 diagram](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jaewilson07/bird-watcher/main/docs/diagrams/04-step.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "## What you're building today\n",
    "\n",
    "The computer learns to ask one question: **is there a bird in this picture?**\n",
    "\n",
    "If yes, it draws a box around the bird and tells you where. If no, it says \"no bird\".\n",
    "\n",
    "By the end of this notebook, every frame will come with an answer: bird or no bird, and where."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "what-is-detection",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4.1 — What is detection?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Detection** means: look at a picture, find the things in it, and say WHERE each thing is.\n",
    "\n",
    "We don't need to know what KIND of bird yet. Just: is one there?\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll use **YOLO** (\"You Only Look Once\"). It's a fast, popular detection model that knows about 80 common things, including \"bird\". A version of it was trained on millions of labeled photos so it can spot things better than you or me.\n",
    "\n",
    "YOLO returns a list of boxes: `[(x, y, width, height), ...]` — one per detected object, plus what it thinks it is."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "install",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ultralytics gives us YOLO. OpenCV helps us draw on the image.\n",
    "!pip install -q ultralytics opencv-python-headless\n",
    "print(\"OK\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "load-model",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4.2 — Load the model\n",
    "\n",
    "The first run downloads the YOLO weights (~6MB). After that it's cached and instant.\n",
    "\n",
    "We're using `yolov8n` — the smallest, fastest version. For a phone-camera frame, it's plenty."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "load-model-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ultralytics import YOLO\n",
    "\n",
    "model = YOLO(\"yolov8n.pt\")  # downloads on first run\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(model.names)} classes\")\n",
    "print(f\"Class index for 'bird': {model.names.index('bird') if 'bird' in model.names else 'not found'}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "load-frame",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4.3 — Grab a frame\n",
    "\n",
    "Reuse the grab function from notebook 03."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "load-frame-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import requests, os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "from IPython.display import display\n",
    "\n",
    "RUNNING_IN_COLAB = \"COLAB_GPU\" in os.environ\n",
    "if RUNNING_IN_COLAB:\n",
    "    SOURCE = \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jaewilson07/bird-watcher/main/data/samples/sample-bird.jpg\"\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    PHONE_IP = \"192.168.1.42\"\n",
    "    SOURCE = f\"http://{PHONE_IP}:8080/photo.jpg\"\n",
    "\n",
    "frame_path = Path(\"data/snapshots/detect-input.jpg\")\n",
    "frame_path.write_bytes(requests.get(SOURCE, timeout=10).content)\n",
    "display(Image.open(frame_path))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "detect",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4.4 — Run detection\n",
    "\n",
    "YOLO returns a result object. For each detection, we get: class name, confidence (0-1), bounding box (xyxy coordinates)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "detect-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = model(frame_path, verbose=False)\n",
    "result = results[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter to just birds (class 14 in COCO)\n",
    "BIRD_CLASS_ID = 14\n",
    "birds = [\n",
    "    box for box in result.boxes\n",
    "    if int(box.cls[0]) == BIRD_CLASS_ID and float(box.conf[0]) > 0.4\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "if not birds:\n",
    "    print(\"no bird\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    for box in birds:\n",
    "        x1, y1, x2, y2 = [int(v) for v in box.xyxy[0]]\n",
    "        conf = float(box.conf[0])\n",
    "        print(f\"bird found at ({x1}, {y1}, {x2}, {y2})  conf={conf:.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "visualize",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4.5 — Draw the box on the image\n",
    "\n",
    "Numbers are useful, but a picture with a box around the bird is way more satisfying."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "visualize-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import cv2\n",
    "\n",
    "img = cv2.imread(str(frame_path))\n",
    "for box in birds:\n",
    "    x1, y1, x2, y2 = [int(v) for v in box.xyxy[0]]\n",
    "    cv2.rectangle(img, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (0, 255, 0), 3)\n",
    "    cv2.putText(img, f\"bird {float(box.conf[0]):.2f}\", (x1, y1 - 10),\n",
    "                cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.9, (0, 255, 0), 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save and show\n",
    "out = Path(\"data/snapshots/detect-output.jpg\")\n",
    "cv2.imwrite(str(out), img)\n",
    "display(Image.open(out))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "wrap-up",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Done?\n",
    "\n",
    "If you saw either:\n",
    "- `bird found at (x, y, x, y)` with a green box on the image, OR\n",
    - `no bird` printed cleanly\n",
    "\n",
    "...then the brain is wired up. 🎉\n",
    "\n",
    "## What's next\n",
    "\n",
    "Issue **#5: Identify species**. We can spot a bird now, but we still don't know what KIND. Time to name names — Robin, Cardinal, Sparrow — with a species classifier. 🐦"
   ]
  }
